Control Statements in C
Control statements control the flow of execution in a C program.
1. Decision Making Statements
Used to make decisions based on conditions.
Examples: if, if-else, else-if ladder, switch
2. Looping Statements
Used to execute a block of code repeatedly.
Examples: for loop, while loop, do-while loop
3. Jump Statements
Used to change the normal flow of execution.
Examples: break, continue, goto, return
Why Control Statements are Important
Control the flow of program
Reduce code repetition
Help in decision making













